1
00:00:18,940 --> 00:00:23,880
♪Only after bloom comes fruit♪

2
00:00:25,290 --> 00:00:29,260
♪Who says glory must fade to the past♪

3
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:37,010
♪Only through thunder
do you reach the clouds♪

4
00:00:38,210 --> 00:00:43,120
♪Who made you the crown of every peak♪

5
00:00:44,650 --> 00:00:47,930
♪I stand at the center of the stage♪

6
00:00:47,930 --> 00:00:51,000
♪My shadow is pinned against the wall♪

7
00:00:51,710 --> 00:00:56,660
♪Facing the light earns every medal♪

8
00:00:57,700 --> 00:01:00,880
♪Little birds,
save your needless pecking♪

9
00:01:00,880 --> 00:01:04,160
♪The open sky rises high♪

10
00:01:04,700 --> 00:01:09,830
♪When night falls,
the moon begins to shine♪

11
00:01:10,600 --> 00:01:13,860
♪I stand in the heart of these lands♪

12
00:01:13,860 --> 00:01:17,220
♪My shadow bears no crown or robe♪

13
00:01:17,630 --> 00:01:23,300
♪Then I know truth needs no disguise♪

14
00:01:23,710 --> 00:01:26,960
♪The green hills see me as I am♪

15
00:01:26,960 --> 00:01:30,290
♪Like dew, lightning,
and moon on the river♪

16
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:34,730
♪Showing me exactly who I am♪

17
00:01:34,730 --> 00:01:35,980
=The Lead=

18
00:01:36,020 --> 00:01:37,940
=Episode 6=

19
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,680
Are you out of your mind?

20
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,160
Playing funereal music so early?

21
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:23,120
Talk properly, okay?

22
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,480
Director Huang told me to play it.

23
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:26,240
He said the morning bell

24
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,480
was for the production team.

25
00:02:27,960 --> 00:02:30,360
So now it's the army wake-up call.

26
00:02:30,920 --> 00:02:32,360
They use a bugle in the army.

27
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:33,680
You're playing a suona horn.

28
00:02:33,680 --> 00:02:35,240
Sounds like you're waking the dead.

29
00:02:35,240 --> 00:02:36,920
It got you out of bed, right?

30
00:02:36,920 --> 00:02:37,760
You...

31
00:02:39,040 --> 00:02:40,480
You are just messing around.

32
00:02:47,880 --> 00:02:49,360
Today is a big day.

33
00:02:49,960 --> 00:02:52,240
You'll each receive a little red booklet.

34
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:54,000
Once you have this booklet,

35
00:02:54,560 --> 00:02:56,200
you'll officially be part of

36
00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:58,400
our troupe family.

37
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,080
Students,

38
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:03,320
we've come from different places.

39
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:05,640
However, we're here for

40
00:03:05,640 --> 00:03:07,040
one shared goal.

41
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:09,560
So what exactly is that goal?

42
00:03:09,960 --> 00:03:14,600
To learn opera well and perform it well.

43
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,640
So,

44
00:03:17,520 --> 00:03:20,480
from now on, take training seriously,

45
00:03:21,320 --> 00:03:24,760
study hard and make progress every day.

46
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:25,960
Applause.

47
00:03:28,040 --> 00:03:30,040
My bad. I'll stop there.

48
00:03:35,600 --> 00:03:36,440
Next,

49
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:38,960
we'll hand out

50
00:03:38,960 --> 00:03:41,680
the trainee IDs and training uniforms.

51
00:03:41,680 --> 00:03:43,800
When you hear your name, come get them.

52
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:46,920
Chu Jiahe.

53
00:03:50,160 --> 00:03:51,000
Here.

54
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:51,920
Thank you.

55
00:03:51,920 --> 00:03:53,320
Don't go yet. Thank the director.

56
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:54,240
Thank you, Director Huang.

57
00:03:54,640 --> 00:03:55,480
Good.

58
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:57,560
Feng Xiaoxiao.

59
00:03:59,080 --> 00:04:00,010
Here, take it.

60
00:04:00,010 --> 00:04:00,880
Thank you, Director Huang.

61
00:04:00,880 --> 00:04:02,040
Come back.

62
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,440
You forgot the booklet.

63
00:04:04,580 --> 00:04:05,440
Hold on to it.

64
00:04:05,440 --> 00:04:06,280
Thank you.

65
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:07,720
Yu Liping.

66
00:04:08,760 --> 00:04:09,880
Thank you, Director.

67
00:04:10,680 --> 00:04:11,520
Alright.

68
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:13,280
Yi Qing'e.

69
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:19,920
Say thank you.

70
00:04:20,520 --> 00:04:21,360
Thank him.

71
00:04:22,040 --> 00:04:22,880
This kid...

72
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,360
She hardly talks as usual?

73
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:25,880
She talks when she's hungry.

74
00:04:26,280 --> 00:04:27,520
So, she ate too much.

75
00:04:28,240 --> 00:04:29,880
Zhang Heiwa.

76
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:33,720
Thanks, Uncle.

77
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:35,440
What?

78
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,400
Huang Zhengjing.

79
00:04:36,780 --> 00:04:37,640
Call him Director.

80
00:04:37,640 --> 00:04:38,480
Director. Director Huang.

81
00:04:38,480 --> 00:04:39,380
How many times must I say it?

82
00:04:39,720 --> 00:04:40,760
The kid's honest.

83
00:04:41,840 --> 00:04:43,040
Like the freshest grass.

84
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:47,680
(Trainee, County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)
I gave you my word, right?

85
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,120
I'm pretty capable, huh?

86
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:52,520
Now you've got this little booklet.

87
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:53,880
That makes you a city person.

88
00:04:54,520 --> 00:04:56,920
You've got the same job as me now.

89
00:04:57,840 --> 00:04:58,840
Work hard, okay?

90
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:01,280
I'll play the drums for you someday.

91
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:02,800
Are you happy?

92
00:05:04,120 --> 00:05:05,520
If you're happy, you should smile.

93
00:05:05,920 --> 00:05:07,280
Why can't I see that you're happy?

94
00:05:15,960 --> 00:05:16,960
What's wrong?

95
00:05:17,680 --> 00:05:18,800
My back hurts.

96
00:05:19,720 --> 00:05:21,920
Go on, take this with you.

97
00:05:22,520 --> 00:05:23,800
Show it to Aunt Hua.

98
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:25,400
Make sure you thank her well.

99
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:26,400
Got it? Go on.

100
00:05:38,880 --> 00:05:39,720
What's wrong?

101
00:05:39,900 --> 00:05:40,740
Nothing.

102
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:41,760
I'm totally fine.

103
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:45,760
This woman has no gentle touch.

104
00:05:50,240 --> 00:05:51,080
How did it happen?

105
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,160
I fell playing basketball.

106
00:06:09,720 --> 00:06:11,160
What were you up to last night?

107
00:06:12,320 --> 00:06:13,480
Drinking with Hu Sanyuan.

108
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:16,120
Since when does drinking hurt the back?

109
00:06:17,520 --> 00:06:18,360
The back?

110
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,000
Whose back got hurt?

111
00:06:20,200 --> 00:06:21,080
Hu Sanyuan's.

112
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:24,360
I'll go check on him.

113
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,920
Take him to the hospital.

114
00:06:33,040 --> 00:06:35,160
Why do I have to take him there?

115
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:37,640
Fine, I'll take him.

116
00:06:53,360 --> 00:07:00,360
♪Grandma tells of the brave old days♪

117
00:07:04,200 --> 00:07:06,080
Yi Qing'e and the other trainees

118
00:07:06,080 --> 00:07:07,840
wore the same clothes

119
00:07:07,840 --> 00:07:08,840
and shoes,

120
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:11,120
carried the same backpacks,

121
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,040
and lived under the same roof.

122
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,840
However,

123
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:16,780
in the other trainees' eyes...

124
00:07:16,780 --> 00:07:17,640
Go.

125
00:07:17,640 --> 00:07:20,760
Yi Qing'e saw the difference.

126
00:07:20,880 --> 00:07:22,520
I'll have my mom bring you more later.

127
00:07:23,120 --> 00:07:24,000
When we were in Beijing,

128
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,320
we bought White Rabbit Creamy Candy.

129
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,160
I brought some with me.

130
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,120
I'll share it with you.

131
00:07:27,120 --> 00:07:27,960
Ms. Hua.

132
00:07:32,480 --> 00:07:33,320
Chu Jiahe,

133
00:07:33,960 --> 00:07:34,840
where are you sleeping?

134
00:07:35,640 --> 00:07:36,480
Over there.

135
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:39,240
Let Laidi sleep next to you.

136
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,600
But Yu Liping and Zhou Yuzhi
want to sleep next to me.

137
00:07:41,600 --> 00:07:42,520
Exactly.

138
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,920
The three of us are good friends.

139
00:07:44,160 --> 00:07:45,760
We've been together since nursery.

140
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:48,320
Why weren't you together before birth?

141
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:50,600
This is the troupe. Follow orders.

142
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:58,880
Line up. Line up.

143
00:07:58,880 --> 00:07:59,720
Hurry.

144
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:00,840
Line up. Line up.

145
00:08:01,520 --> 00:08:02,360
Hurry it up.

146
00:08:02,920 --> 00:08:03,760
Catch up.

147
00:08:05,340 --> 00:08:06,200
I'll sleep here.

148
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,040
Hurry.

149
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:08,560
That's by the door.

150
00:08:08,560 --> 00:08:10,360
It's windy there. Cold in winter too.

151
00:08:10,800 --> 00:08:11,640
I'm not scared.

152
00:08:14,560 --> 00:08:15,400
Quiet!

153
00:08:16,160 --> 00:08:17,640
Line up. Line up!

154
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:18,480
Move!

155
00:08:18,780 --> 00:08:19,640
Move!

156
00:08:19,640 --> 00:08:20,920
By height. By height.

157
00:08:22,040 --> 00:08:24,840
Short ones here, tall ones there. Move.

158
00:08:25,640 --> 00:08:27,760
Are you deaf or what?

159
00:08:27,760 --> 00:08:28,840
Stop chatting!

160
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:39,000
Look at the state you're all in.

161
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,120
Every one of you is all over the place.

162
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,560
You're a total mess.

163
00:08:43,160 --> 00:08:44,320
This trainee class

164
00:08:44,840 --> 00:08:46,250
has to be run like the military.

165
00:08:46,250 --> 00:08:47,120
Hurry.

166
00:08:47,120 --> 00:08:47,980
- Hurry!
- Look...

167
00:08:47,980 --> 00:08:48,860
You're the slowest one here.

168
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,280
Hurry.

169
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,000
You would be late

170
00:08:52,120 --> 00:08:53,480
even for eating poop.

171
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,340
Watch your mouth.

172
00:08:54,340 --> 00:08:55,200
You okay?

173
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,160
I'm eating poop here?

174
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,120
I'm training them, okay?

175
00:09:02,360 --> 00:09:03,320
You blockhead,

176
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,280
where are you standing?

177
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,200
Go to the boy's line!

178
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:10,640
Director, I...

179
00:09:10,640 --> 00:09:11,510
You go first.

180
00:09:11,510 --> 00:09:12,360
Okay.

181
00:09:14,560 --> 00:09:17,040
My name is He Dachui.

182
00:09:17,680 --> 00:09:19,040
Starting today,

183
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:20,480
I'm the class teacher.

184
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:23,360
Feng Xiaoxiao, Chu Jiahe, step out.

185
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:24,720
From now on,

186
00:09:24,880 --> 00:09:28,560
Feng Xiaoxiao is the
class monitor for the boys,

187
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:32,920
and Chu Jiahe is the monitor for the girls.

188
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,960
Alright, back in line.

189
00:09:36,240 --> 00:09:39,800
Go to your monitors first
if anything comes up.

190
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:41,880
- Zhang Yinwa!
- If I can't handle it,

191
00:09:41,880 --> 00:09:43,480
I'll go ask Director Huang.

192
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:47,920
Let's welcome Director Huang to speak.

193
00:09:49,960 --> 00:09:51,200
Don't you know how to clap?

194
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:52,040
Clap.

195
00:09:52,640 --> 00:09:53,560
A little more energy.

196
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,440
Students,

197
00:09:59,240 --> 00:10:01,160
it's your first lesson
after joining the troupe.

198
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,520
I'll teach you this part myself.

199
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,880
Today's lesson is this.

200
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:09,280
At ease.

201
00:10:10,120 --> 00:10:12,480
Attention. And count off.

202
00:10:13,080 --> 00:10:14,280
I'll show you first.

203
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:16,200
At ease.

204
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,040
Attention.

205
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:22,320
At ease.

206
00:10:24,920 --> 00:10:25,760
Attention.

207
00:10:37,200 --> 00:10:38,560
Let's find somewhere to talk.

208
00:10:40,120 --> 00:10:40,960
Sure.

209
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:44,300
(Ningzhou People's Hospital)

210
00:11:06,560 --> 00:11:07,640
Are you two together or not?

211
00:11:12,840 --> 00:11:14,880
We rehearse together and perform together.

212
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:18,080
Does that revolutionary camaraderie

213
00:11:18,600 --> 00:11:20,200
count as being together to you?

214
00:11:21,480 --> 00:11:23,440
If you're a man, own what you did.

215
00:11:28,280 --> 00:11:30,440
Then should we go to the hospital again?

216
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:31,330
For what?

217
00:11:31,330 --> 00:11:32,230
To ask the hospital

218
00:11:32,230 --> 00:11:33,920
if they can do a virginity test.

219
00:11:34,180 --> 00:11:35,040
If they can,

220
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,000
I can prove to you my virginity.

221
00:11:37,000 --> 00:11:38,600
No one will believe you're still a virgin.

222
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,360
I'm embarrassed to admit it.

223
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:44,240
Keep your distance from Hua Caixiang.

224
00:11:45,520 --> 00:11:47,040
Just transfer her away.

225
00:11:47,880 --> 00:11:49,160
Then the distance issue will be solved.

226
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:50,720
You think I haven't tried?

227
00:11:50,720 --> 00:11:52,320
I found her a post, but she won't go.

228
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:54,440
Then how about transferring me away?

229
00:11:55,880 --> 00:11:57,120
You're such a jerk.

230
00:11:58,160 --> 00:11:59,200
Yeah, I think so too.

231
00:12:02,560 --> 00:12:03,560
I'll trust you this one time.

232
00:12:06,440 --> 00:12:07,840
Sorry about last night.

233
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,840
Harm by mistake.

234
00:12:18,880 --> 00:12:19,720
It's okay.

235
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:21,920
I'm used to getting harmed by mistake.

236
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,200
What is it?

237
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:45,660
(A Happy Family)

238
00:12:46,280 --> 00:12:47,120
Those idiots.

239
00:12:48,280 --> 00:12:49,840
Don't get the wrong idea.

240
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:51,960
I'll let them explain.

241
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:56,080
Take that photo off the cabinet.

242
00:12:56,480 --> 00:12:57,360
Why?

243
00:12:57,360 --> 00:12:58,260
That's my photo.

244
00:12:58,260 --> 00:12:59,120
Who allowed you to put it there?

245
00:12:59,120 --> 00:13:00,600
Aren't you supposed to feel proud?

246
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:01,440
Nonsense!

247
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,680
Take it down right now.

248
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,560
At ease.

249
00:13:26,880 --> 00:13:27,720
Quick notes.

250
00:13:28,120 --> 00:13:31,640
In the end, this stage is yours.

251
00:13:31,640 --> 00:13:33,640
Yes, yours. It's all yours.

252
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:35,360
As for today's training,

253
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:38,480
most of you did pretty well.

254
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,920
The improvement is obvious.

255
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:44,880
A few of you still need to work harder.

256
00:13:46,000 --> 00:13:47,040
That's all for the notes.

257
00:13:48,760 --> 00:13:50,360
That's it for today's training.

258
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:52,520
Thanks for your hard work, everyone.

259
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:53,680
Dismissed.

260
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:55,200
Director,

261
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:56,320
have some water.

262
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:57,640
You must be tired.

263
00:14:00,840 --> 00:14:01,920
What are you looking at?

264
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:03,960
Why not go play with them?

265
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:04,960
I don't know how.

266
00:14:05,480 --> 00:14:06,400
Not a single one?

267
00:14:08,520 --> 00:14:09,440
You know how to eat?

268
00:14:10,840 --> 00:14:12,240
Cut the nonsense.

269
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,360
Extra, extra!

270
00:14:13,640 --> 00:14:19,560
Hu Sanyuan was caught by the police!

271
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:22,440
He's her uncle!

272
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,280
Caught for having an illicit affair!

273
00:14:24,680 --> 00:14:25,680
Extra, extra!

274
00:14:25,960 --> 00:14:27,680
Hu Sanyuan was caught by the police!

275
00:14:27,940 --> 00:14:28,800
Extra, extra!

276
00:14:28,800 --> 00:14:30,160
Her uncle was caught by the police.

277
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:32,000
What do you know? Stop talking nonsense.

278
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:32,840
An illicit affair?

279
00:14:33,000 --> 00:14:34,080
Extra, extra!

280
00:14:34,080 --> 00:14:36,000
Hu Sanyuan was caught by the police!

281
00:14:36,880 --> 00:14:37,800
What is an illicit affair?

282
00:14:38,120 --> 00:14:39,280
Extra, extra!

283
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:41,280
Hu Sanyuan was caught by the police!

284
00:14:41,640 --> 00:14:42,720
Extra, extra!

285
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:45,000
Hu Sanyuan was caught by the police!

286
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:48,600
♪Fragrance of red plum blossoms♪

287
00:14:48,600 --> 00:14:49,520
Yi Qing'e!

288
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,640
Yi Qing'e, don't go out!

289
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:52,680
Yi Qing'e!

290
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:54,240
Come back!

291
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:55,680
Yi Qing'e!

292
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:56,960
Don't run!

293
00:14:56,960 --> 00:14:57,820
Why are you running?

294
00:14:57,820 --> 00:14:58,960
Careful, don't fall!

295
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,200
Don't run. Where are you going?

296
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,280
Yi Qing'e.

297
00:15:02,280 --> 00:15:03,280
Stop.

298
00:15:03,280 --> 00:15:04,200
What are you doing?

299
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,040
Where's your exit pass?

300
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:08,640
No exit pass, no going out.

301
00:15:08,640 --> 00:15:09,600
Let go!

302
00:15:09,600 --> 00:15:10,920
- No.
- You can't go out.

303
00:15:11,200 --> 00:15:12,120
Stay out of it.

304
00:15:12,120 --> 00:15:13,680
I'm the monitor. I can stop you.

305
00:15:13,680 --> 00:15:14,520
Exactly.

306
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,640
Why are you going out anyway?

307
00:15:16,960 --> 00:15:18,160
She's going to see her uncle.

308
00:15:18,160 --> 00:15:19,600
Her uncle went to a fair

309
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:20,680
and got caught somehow.

310
00:15:20,680 --> 00:15:21,680
You idiot.

311
00:15:21,680 --> 00:15:23,160
That's not what I said.

312
00:15:23,160 --> 00:15:24,720
It's an illicit affair!

313
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:25,720
Watch your mouth!

314
00:15:25,960 --> 00:15:26,970
Quiet.

315
00:15:26,970 --> 00:15:28,280
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)

316
00:15:28,280 --> 00:15:29,280
Go back, all of you.

317
00:15:31,320 --> 00:15:32,320
(A Happy Family)
Here's what

318
00:15:32,320 --> 00:15:33,160
happened.

319
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,720
Hu Sanyuan and Zhang Guangrong

320
00:15:36,080 --> 00:15:37,640
were passing the photo studio

321
00:15:37,640 --> 00:15:39,880
when they saw this photo in the window.

322
00:15:40,720 --> 00:15:43,240
Zhang Guangrong claimed he got upset

323
00:15:43,640 --> 00:15:44,680
and smashed their glass.

324
00:15:46,160 --> 00:15:47,480
What about Hu Sanyuan?

325
00:15:48,160 --> 00:15:49,000
Stand still.

326
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,800
Hu Sanyuan

327
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:54,120
demanded that the studio
destroy the negative film

328
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:55,360
and apologize to Zhang Guangrong.

329
00:15:55,960 --> 00:15:57,400
They ignored him

330
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:59,000
and kept holding on to Zhang.

331
00:15:59,000 --> 00:15:59,920
So, Hu

332
00:16:00,040 --> 00:16:01,160
got mad

333
00:16:01,440 --> 00:16:02,600
and smashed their counter.

334
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,920
What they did was way too serious.

335
00:16:05,240 --> 00:16:06,320
They must be punished severely.

336
00:16:07,840 --> 00:16:09,640
They put my photo up there

337
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:11,120
without my permission.

338
00:16:11,120 --> 00:16:12,440
Wasn't what they did serious?

339
00:16:13,040 --> 00:16:14,480
In their defense,

340
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,000
if you weren't family,

341
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:17,240
why would you have taken that photo?

342
00:16:17,680 --> 00:16:19,080
And they said,

343
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,400
"You played a fake couple onstage,

344
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:23,400
so why not tear down the stage too?"

345
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,560
Then they said,

346
00:16:26,120 --> 00:16:27,120
"That display window

347
00:16:27,120 --> 00:16:28,960
isn't for just anyone.

348
00:16:28,960 --> 00:16:29,920
If your photo

349
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:31,440
made it up there,

350
00:16:31,440 --> 00:16:34,280
you should feel honored and proud."

351
00:16:34,280 --> 00:16:35,640
So, that's on us?

352
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:38,520
If you hadn't posed together,

353
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:39,920
there wouldn't have been this photo.

354
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,240
And if, when you took it,

355
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:42,560
you weren't holding grain,

356
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:44,080
the photo studio wouldn't have used you

357
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:46,000
to promote the new look and spirit

358
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:47,120
of socialism.

359
00:16:48,240 --> 00:16:50,160
So whose responsibility is that?

360
00:16:51,080 --> 00:16:51,960
Comrade officer,

361
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:55,720
I think this photo

362
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:57,440
has a symbolic meaning.

363
00:16:58,420 --> 00:16:59,280
The people in it

364
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:01,400
don't stand for anyone specific.

365
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,800
They stand for

366
00:17:04,520 --> 00:17:06,120
the happy masses.

367
00:17:07,080 --> 00:17:08,400
The director is absolutely right.

368
00:17:08,720 --> 00:17:09,560
Comrade officer,

369
00:17:09,680 --> 00:17:10,640
this is a political incident.

370
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,400
It's a serious conflict between
us and the enemy!

371
00:17:12,680 --> 00:17:13,920
Don't politicize it!

372
00:17:13,920 --> 00:17:15,240
- What's wrong?
- What's wrong?

373
00:17:15,480 --> 00:17:16,320
Am I wrong?

374
00:17:16,320 --> 00:17:17,320
Are you the police?

375
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,720
Comrade officer,

376
00:17:20,720 --> 00:17:23,080
I think Director Huang is right.

377
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:25,640
He isn't Hu Sanyuan.

378
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:27,880
He's one of the happy masses.

379
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:30,840
Calling the happy masses the enemy

380
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:32,400
is just stirring things up.

381
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:34,520
You're the real enemy here.

382
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:42,080
We don't agree with you either.

383
00:17:42,400 --> 00:17:44,480
The photo studio shares the blame.

384
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:46,880
This is an internal dispute.

385
00:17:47,720 --> 00:17:48,800
Comrade, this matter

386
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:51,280
has had a really bad influence

387
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,600
on our troupe.

388
00:17:52,960 --> 00:17:53,840
We can't just ignore it.

389
00:17:54,240 --> 00:17:55,360
Be quiet.

390
00:17:57,000 --> 00:17:58,600
If you want to deal with it, go back

391
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:00,040
and handle it yourselves.

392
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,080
Sure.

393
00:18:01,400 --> 00:18:02,520
I advise you

394
00:18:02,840 --> 00:18:04,240
to take those two and apologize.

395
00:18:04,240 --> 00:18:05,080
Pay some compensation.

396
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:06,240
Be more polite.

397
00:18:06,240 --> 00:18:07,880
Keep it small and smooth it over.

398
00:18:08,560 --> 00:18:09,720
What does that have to do with me?

399
00:18:10,000 --> 00:18:11,840
On the surface, nothing.

400
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:15,080
But think it through, it matters a lot.

401
00:18:15,360 --> 00:18:17,360
You're a known figure in our county.

402
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,320
Your influence is huge.

403
00:18:18,320 --> 00:18:19,360
They know where the line is.

404
00:18:19,360 --> 00:18:20,280
They won't mess with you lightly.

405
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:35,480
The tricycle's right here.

406
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,480
Get in.

407
00:18:54,940 --> 00:19:00,940
(Chengguan Police Station, Ningzhou County)

408
00:19:01,300 --> 00:19:03,820
♪Blood and tears, all on one ledger♪

409
00:19:03,820 --> 00:19:06,620
♪You must stand tall and aim high♪

410
00:19:06,620 --> 00:19:09,460
♪And settle every score with the enemy♪

411
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,080
Director.

412
00:19:12,720 --> 00:19:13,960
Director Huang, have some melon.

413
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:18,960
Just like they say, time reveals all.

414
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,720
The sneaky business between Hu Sanyuan

415
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:22,640
and Hua Caixiang is confirmed.

416
00:19:22,920 --> 00:19:24,120
We need to really shame those two.

417
00:19:26,920 --> 00:19:29,360
Yinwa, about that anonymous letter,

418
00:19:29,360 --> 00:19:30,960
you believe now that Director Huang

419
00:19:30,960 --> 00:19:32,160
was set up by someone, right?

420
00:19:33,160 --> 00:19:36,040
I'm telling you, Hu Sanyuan is bad news.

421
00:19:36,040 --> 00:19:38,080
Don't let him use you again.

422
00:19:38,640 --> 00:19:40,280
Someone right now

423
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,000
must really hate Hu Sanyuan.

424
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:44,720
Why glaring at me?

425
00:19:44,720 --> 00:19:45,800
Are you Someone?

426
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:53,920
See?

427
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,770
(That last chime indicated)
This fine watch

428
00:19:55,770 --> 00:19:57,320
(9 P.M.)
is spot on.

429
00:19:57,320 --> 00:19:58,840
(Beijing time.)
Let me see.

430
00:19:59,240 --> 00:20:00,080
Look.

431
00:20:00,280 --> 00:20:01,120
How accurate!

432
00:20:01,920 --> 00:20:03,560
No wonder it costs so much.

433
00:20:03,560 --> 00:20:04,680
Its standards are really high.

434
00:20:04,680 --> 00:20:06,880
Always synced with Beijing time.

435
00:20:08,400 --> 00:20:09,240
Ma'am.

436
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:11,520
♪During the labor strike♪

437
00:20:11,520 --> 00:20:12,400
What is it?

438
00:20:12,960 --> 00:20:13,880
What are you doing here?

439
00:20:14,440 --> 00:20:15,360
I heard your wife was sick.

440
00:20:15,360 --> 00:20:16,320
So I came to see her.

441
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:17,880
And you are?

442
00:20:18,520 --> 00:20:20,640
Ma'am, I'm Mi Lan.

443
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:22,680
I've wanted to visit you before.

444
00:20:22,960 --> 00:20:24,720
But then I worried people would talk.

445
00:20:24,720 --> 00:20:25,560
So I didn't come.

446
00:20:26,080 --> 00:20:27,160
Talk about what?

447
00:20:27,600 --> 00:20:29,160
That I was cozying up to Director Huang.

448
00:20:29,440 --> 00:20:30,880
But then I thought it over.

449
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:33,360
If gossip kept me from seeing you,

450
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:34,960
then it'd mean I had something to hide.

451
00:20:34,960 --> 00:20:35,800
So I came after all.

452
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:38,440
You're right about that.

453
00:20:38,800 --> 00:20:40,600
A person should be open and honest.

454
00:20:40,600 --> 00:20:41,640
I'm not some ghost.

455
00:20:42,040 --> 00:20:43,880
Why does a person have to avoid me? Right?

456
00:20:43,880 --> 00:20:44,720
That's right.

457
00:20:45,120 --> 00:20:46,200
I brought you some pastries.

458
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:47,060
So kind of you.

459
00:20:47,060 --> 00:20:48,560
Come on, sit.

460
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:52,080
Ma'am, are you feeling better now?

461
00:20:52,080 --> 00:20:53,000
I'm fine now.

462
00:20:53,440 --> 00:20:54,920
Have some watermelon. Just sliced.

463
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:55,760
Thanks.

464
00:21:03,360 --> 00:21:05,000
Why are there so many bats?

465
00:21:05,560 --> 00:21:07,360
I heard before we got here,

466
00:21:07,360 --> 00:21:09,920
this place was full of rats and bats.

467
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:12,680
Who said that?

468
00:21:12,680 --> 00:21:16,720
I heard there used to be ghosts here.

469
00:21:19,800 --> 00:21:21,120
Shut it.

470
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:24,720
Come on, follow my lead.

471
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:29,960
One, two, three.

472
00:21:29,960 --> 00:21:30,800
Throw.

473
00:21:44,680 --> 00:21:45,720
I'm treating everyone to candy.

474
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:47,960
No hurry.

475
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:51,000
Everyone gets one.

476
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:51,920
No hurry.

477
00:21:52,320 --> 00:21:53,320
No hurry.

478
00:21:53,320 --> 00:21:54,760
There's enough for everyone.

479
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,280
This is candy from Beijing.

480
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:58,160
Give me the wrappers when you're done.

481
00:21:58,520 --> 00:21:59,360
Sweet, huh?

482
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:00,360
Yeah.

483
00:22:00,360 --> 00:22:02,920
Candy from Beijing is sweeter.

484
00:22:02,920 --> 00:22:04,400
Exactly. Way sweeter.

485
00:22:04,400 --> 00:22:05,260
Give me back the wrappers.

486
00:22:05,260 --> 00:22:06,100
Okay.

487
00:22:07,360 --> 00:22:08,920
Who here has been to Beijing?

488
00:22:08,920 --> 00:22:10,160
No one.

489
00:22:10,880 --> 00:22:11,720
I have.

490
00:22:12,260 --> 00:22:13,120
For real?

491
00:22:13,120 --> 00:22:15,040
I even saw Tian'anmen in Beijing.

492
00:22:15,040 --> 00:22:16,320
That's amazing.

493
00:22:17,040 --> 00:22:18,320
Did you see Chairman Mao?

494
00:22:18,640 --> 00:22:19,520
I did.

495
00:22:19,880 --> 00:22:21,600
I even saluted him.

496
00:22:21,600 --> 00:22:22,460
Really?

497
00:22:22,460 --> 00:22:23,440
For real?

498
00:22:23,440 --> 00:22:24,280
Let me show you.

499
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:27,960
What's this?

500
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:29,640
Look.

501
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:31,360
The photo of me saluting.

502
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,200
That's Tian'anmen.

503
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:38,860
I want to go too.

504
00:22:39,320 --> 00:22:41,320
♪I Love Beijing Tian'anmen♪

505
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:45,080
♪The sun rises above Tian'anmen♪

506
00:22:45,360 --> 00:22:47,320
♪The great leader Chairman Mao♪

507
00:22:47,320 --> 00:22:50,680
♪Leads all of us forward♪

508
00:22:51,400 --> 00:22:55,200
♪I Love Beijing Tian'anmen♪

509
00:22:55,320 --> 00:22:59,000
♪The sun rises above Tian'anmen♪

510
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:03,040
♪The great leader Chairman Mao♪

511
00:23:03,040 --> 00:23:06,520
♪Leads all of us forward♪

512
00:23:08,480 --> 00:23:09,320
Bayi.

513
00:23:11,440 --> 00:23:12,280
Bayi.

514
00:23:46,520 --> 00:23:48,280
You, stop right there!

515
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:49,920
Stop right there! Don't run!

516
00:23:51,720 --> 00:23:52,640
Stop right there!

517
00:23:52,940 --> 00:23:53,800
Stop!

518
00:23:53,800 --> 00:23:54,640
Bayi.

519
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:55,800
You little rascal.

520
00:23:55,800 --> 00:23:57,200
I'll knock you out!

521
00:23:58,080 --> 00:23:58,920
Don't run!

522
00:23:59,400 --> 00:24:00,240
Stop!

523
00:24:01,040 --> 00:24:01,880
Come here!

524
00:24:44,200 --> 00:24:45,820
Run!

525
00:24:45,820 --> 00:24:46,660
Where do you think

526
00:24:46,660 --> 00:24:47,660
you're going?

527
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,040
Stop!

528
00:24:49,240 --> 00:24:50,640
Run!

529
00:24:50,880 --> 00:24:51,920
Stop!

530
00:24:53,680 --> 00:24:55,120
Run. Run!

531
00:24:58,240 --> 00:24:59,320
Go. Go.

532
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:00,240
Go.

533
00:25:00,360 --> 00:25:01,200
Move.

534
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:07,960
Laidi.

535
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:09,240
Laidi!

536
00:25:14,200 --> 00:25:15,200
Why'd you come out here?

537
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,520
Are you okay?

538
00:25:17,800 --> 00:25:18,640
I'm fine.

539
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:19,760
Where's Er Laizi?

540
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,560
Him?

541
00:25:21,960 --> 00:25:23,400
I lost him in the ditch.

542
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:25,280
What happened?

543
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:27,000
I smashed his window.

544
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,440
Why?

545
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,560
He ran his mouth about your uncle

546
00:25:31,560 --> 00:25:32,920
having an illicit affair.

547
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:35,520
You stood up for me?

548
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:37,880
You've done the same for me.

549
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,880
What will you do now?

550
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:44,640
I won't go back.

551
00:25:45,120 --> 00:25:46,960
If I do, Er Laizi will beat me to death,

552
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:48,160
or my dad will beat me to death.

553
00:25:48,560 --> 00:25:49,440
Then where are you going?

554
00:25:50,040 --> 00:25:50,880
Back to my hometown.

555
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:52,280
I'm leaving in a bit.

556
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,200
Tell my dad for me.

557
00:25:56,120 --> 00:25:57,200
Not scared of the dark?

558
00:25:58,560 --> 00:25:59,400
No.

559
00:26:02,080 --> 00:26:03,160
Do you know the way?

560
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,320
Of course, I do.

561
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:09,960
Once you leave,

562
00:26:11,000 --> 00:26:13,000
no one will talk to me anymore.

563
00:26:15,280 --> 00:26:16,640
You've got so many classmates.

564
00:26:17,160 --> 00:26:18,240
You'll get close to them.

565
00:26:20,040 --> 00:26:21,000
Don't cry.

566
00:26:26,040 --> 00:26:27,640
Do you know the way to Jiuyangou?

567
00:26:29,440 --> 00:26:30,320
Why ask?

568
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:33,280
I want to leave too.

569
00:26:34,720 --> 00:26:36,800
You silly, why go back?

570
00:26:37,280 --> 00:26:38,600
Perform well in opera.

571
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:40,520
Be the lead.

572
00:26:40,960 --> 00:26:42,400
Have them play bit parts for you.

573
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:44,600
You can't leave.

574
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:47,200
We'll see who laughs last.

575
00:26:48,400 --> 00:26:49,320
Stop crying.

576
00:26:51,840 --> 00:26:52,680
It's for you.

577
00:26:53,600 --> 00:26:55,040
Remember to take care of yourself.

578
00:26:56,560 --> 00:26:58,080
There you are, you little punk.

579
00:27:01,680 --> 00:27:02,640
Stop right there.

580
00:27:05,320 --> 00:27:06,360
I'm not silly.

581
00:27:08,800 --> 00:27:10,200
Bayi left.

582
00:27:10,520 --> 00:27:12,080
He slipped away.

583
00:27:12,600 --> 00:27:14,840
Yi Qing'e didn't want him to leave.

584
00:27:15,640 --> 00:27:17,510
Since joining the theater troupe,

585
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:20,000
this was her first goodbye.

586
00:28:08,000 --> 00:28:08,880
Still up?

587
00:28:14,040 --> 00:28:15,400
Bayi went back to his hometown.

588
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:18,200
He asked me to tell you.

589
00:28:21,040 --> 00:28:21,880
Is he okay?

590
00:28:22,840 --> 00:28:23,680
He's fine.

591
00:28:25,400 --> 00:28:26,240
Okay.

592
00:28:28,560 --> 00:28:29,440
I'm sorry.

593
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:33,160
Bayi was only standing up for me.

594
00:28:33,160 --> 00:28:36,200
He used a slingshot
to smash Er Laizi's window.

595
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:42,960
It's not your fault.

596
00:28:43,320 --> 00:28:45,640
It's Bayi's fault for playing dirty.

597
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:47,320
He should've been more like you,

598
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:48,800
gone after Er Laizi with a stick.

599
00:28:49,200 --> 00:28:50,200
That's what makes

600
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:51,040
a real man.

601
00:28:51,040 --> 00:28:51,880
Right?

602
00:28:52,320 --> 00:28:53,160
It's okay.

603
00:31:11,000 --> 00:31:11,920
Zhang Guangrong.

604
00:31:21,880 --> 00:31:22,960
Zhang Guangrong.

605
00:31:28,400 --> 00:31:29,240
Let's

606
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:31,800
get divorced.

607
00:31:42,560 --> 00:31:44,000
The truth is finally out.

608
00:31:48,600 --> 00:31:50,040
Being with you,

609
00:31:51,320 --> 00:31:53,400
I can't play the role of wife well.

610
00:31:55,080 --> 00:31:55,920
I'm tired.

611
00:32:04,840 --> 00:32:05,800
That jerk

612
00:32:08,280 --> 00:32:09,680
even had the nerve to say

613
00:32:10,200 --> 00:32:11,200
he was still a virgin.

614
00:32:13,880 --> 00:32:15,520
I really didn't know that.

615
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:17,240
I swear to heaven,

616
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:18,560
up to this moment,

617
00:32:18,920 --> 00:32:20,240
I've only ever been with you.

618
00:32:21,280 --> 00:32:22,120
It's just...

619
00:32:25,120 --> 00:32:26,920
It's just, maybe...

620
00:32:27,240 --> 00:32:28,520
Haven't I treated you well?

621
00:32:29,280 --> 00:32:30,160
You have.

622
00:32:32,600 --> 00:32:34,120
Have I ever done you wrong?

623
00:32:34,600 --> 00:32:35,440
No.

624
00:32:35,960 --> 00:32:37,400
Other than not playing drums,

625
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:41,160
what part of me is worse than him?

626
00:32:42,800 --> 00:32:44,240
Besides knowing how to drum,

627
00:32:45,080 --> 00:32:46,320
he's nowhere near as good as you.

628
00:32:47,240 --> 00:32:48,160
Then why do you...

629
00:32:51,080 --> 00:32:52,600
I can't really explain it.

630
00:32:53,960 --> 00:32:55,240
But I need to know.

631
00:32:58,360 --> 00:33:00,320
Maybe when I'm with him...

632
00:33:01,960 --> 00:33:02,920
I have a soul.

633
00:33:06,520 --> 00:33:07,360
What does that mean?

634
00:33:12,280 --> 00:33:14,720
You don't perform. You can't understand.

635
00:33:21,240 --> 00:33:22,280
I'm going back to work tomorrow.

636
00:33:48,120 --> 00:33:49,600
Give me some time

637
00:33:50,360 --> 00:33:51,200
to think.

638
00:34:50,400 --> 00:34:51,240
(Ningzhou County Qinqiang Opera Troupe)
Why so early?

639
00:34:51,440 --> 00:34:52,520
Something came up at the factory.

640
00:34:52,980 --> 00:34:53,840
Goodbye, Master Gou.

641
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:54,680
Take care.

642
00:34:54,860 --> 00:34:55,720
Thanks, Master Gou.

643
00:34:55,720 --> 00:34:56,560
Alright.

644
00:35:00,480 --> 00:35:02,080
Okay, head back. I'm leaving.

645
00:35:02,080 --> 00:35:03,160
I'll see you off at the bus station.

646
00:35:03,560 --> 00:35:04,400
No need.

647
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:11,240
I'm sorry.

648
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:53,800
Stop the noise. So annoying!

649
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:23,240
Laidi.

650
00:36:28,080 --> 00:36:29,000
Why was she here?

651
00:36:53,680 --> 00:36:54,520
Still asleep?

652
00:36:55,820 --> 00:36:56,680
Get up!

653
00:36:56,680 --> 00:36:57,560
Up, up.

654
00:36:57,920 --> 00:36:58,760
Still sleeping?

655
00:36:59,080 --> 00:37:00,280
Up. Get up!

656
00:37:06,440 --> 00:37:07,280
Get up.

657
00:37:07,560 --> 00:37:08,600
What?

658
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:09,880
Get up.

659
00:37:10,120 --> 00:37:11,000
Come on, get up.

660
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:12,360
Zhou Yuzhi.

661
00:37:12,360 --> 00:37:13,400
Come on, get up.

662
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,200
You came here to study opera,

663
00:37:15,200 --> 00:37:16,040
not to sleep all day.

664
00:37:16,140 --> 00:37:17,000
Hurry up.

665
00:37:17,000 --> 00:37:18,030
- Where are my socks?
- Get up, quick.

666
00:37:18,220 --> 00:37:19,080
You have them.

667
00:37:19,080 --> 00:37:20,600
Where are my pants?

668
00:37:20,600 --> 00:37:22,160
Over there.

669
00:37:49,520 --> 00:37:50,560
Seriously though,

670
00:37:50,800 --> 00:37:52,280
they've got some nerve.

671
00:37:59,720 --> 00:38:00,640
Zhang Guangrong is gone.

672
00:38:01,320 --> 00:38:03,000
He went back to his work unit early.

673
00:38:03,520 --> 00:38:04,920
Just because of that photo?

674
00:38:06,680 --> 00:38:07,640
I already told him.

675
00:38:08,640 --> 00:38:09,480
I want a divorce.

676
00:38:22,920 --> 00:38:25,760
One, two, three, four.

677
00:38:25,760 --> 00:38:27,160
Ningzhou County Troupe's

678
00:38:27,560 --> 00:38:30,440
class of 1976 training program

679
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:31,720
is now open.

680
00:38:32,640 --> 00:38:34,560
The trainees got up before dawn.

681
00:38:34,720 --> 00:38:36,360
They lined up and called roll,

682
00:38:36,560 --> 00:38:40,280
then ran out of town
for vocal projection practice.

683
00:38:41,400 --> 00:38:43,320
Back when she herded sheep in Jiuyangou,

684
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:47,600
Yi Qing'e often shouted at the distant hills

685
00:38:48,400 --> 00:38:51,520
and listened for the echo coming back.

686
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:52,920
But now,

687
00:38:53,200 --> 00:38:55,520
the moment she shouted,
she went numb all over,

688
00:38:55,520 --> 00:38:57,040
and her skin prickled.

689
00:38:58,480 --> 00:39:00,560
She felt like she sounded like a donkey.

690
00:39:01,440 --> 00:39:05,040
And Heiwa sounded like one, too.

691
00:39:06,360 --> 00:39:07,760
No one expected that

692
00:39:08,040 --> 00:39:10,120
training would be so hard.

693
00:39:10,440 --> 00:39:13,000
Leg stretches, backbends, splits...

694
00:39:13,280 --> 00:39:16,600
Every move hurt to the core.

695
00:39:17,320 --> 00:39:18,280
During training,

696
00:39:18,360 --> 00:39:20,880
everyone screamed in agony like a pig,

697
00:39:21,160 --> 00:39:23,920
and cried like a buzzing hive.

698
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:27,480
Except for Yi Qing'e, who stayed silent.

699
00:39:28,320 --> 00:39:30,360
She'd learned to endure young.

700
00:39:31,240 --> 00:39:32,080
Go on.

701
00:39:33,440 --> 00:39:34,440
Why are you shaking?

702
00:39:35,160 --> 00:39:36,000
Push harder.

703
00:39:36,440 --> 00:39:37,280
Harder.

704
00:39:37,280 --> 00:39:38,120
Backwards.

705
00:39:38,860 --> 00:39:39,720
Head up.

706
00:39:39,720 --> 00:39:40,840
I can't hold it anymore.

707
00:39:41,400 --> 00:39:42,680
Lift your waist.

708
00:39:42,680 --> 00:39:44,040
Push your hips, come on.

709
00:39:52,800 --> 00:39:53,920
How many days are in a year?

710
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,640
Three hundred sixty-five.

711
00:39:56,640 --> 00:39:57,760
What about ten years?

712
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:00,520
Three thousand six hundred fifty days.

713
00:40:00,520 --> 00:40:01,380
Hands up.

714
00:40:01,380 --> 00:40:02,380
I'm telling you all,

715
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:05,400
from now on, these 3,650 days,

716
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:07,120
every day will be like today.

717
00:40:09,920 --> 00:40:10,760
Think this is hard?

718
00:40:11,360 --> 00:40:13,280
Think of the Red Army's Long March.

719
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:14,560
Think you're tired?

720
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:16,920
Think of the revolutionary elders.

721
00:40:16,920 --> 00:40:18,840
You have to tough it out, all of it.

722
00:40:21,560 --> 00:40:23,360
Director Huang. Deputy Director Zhu.

723
00:40:24,040 --> 00:40:24,920
Say hello to the cadres.

724
00:40:25,400 --> 00:40:27,800
Hello, cadres.

725
00:40:28,590 --> 00:40:29,510
Good, very good.

726
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:30,960
Alright, keep going.

727
00:40:30,960 --> 00:40:32,120
Sure. Sure, Director.

728
00:40:35,360 --> 00:40:36,200
Down.

729
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:37,840
See that?

730
00:40:37,840 --> 00:40:40,440
He Dachui's drumming is half-baked.

731
00:40:40,440 --> 00:40:42,160
He's pretty convincing as the class teacher.

732
00:40:42,520 --> 00:40:44,440
He used to be an actor.

733
00:40:45,680 --> 00:40:46,680
Why'd he switch careers?

734
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:49,200
His look wasn't good enough.

735
00:40:49,760 --> 00:40:50,760
His look? Well...

736
00:40:50,760 --> 00:40:52,360
The role of Chou fits him well.

737
00:40:52,360 --> 00:40:54,120
He can't handle hardship.

738
00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:56,160
This job takes grit, you know?

739
00:40:56,160 --> 00:40:58,240
Grit, grit, grit.

740
00:40:58,240 --> 00:40:59,480
In our line of work,

741
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:01,160
you've gotta tough it out.

742
00:41:01,600 --> 00:41:02,760
He can't take hardship himself,

743
00:41:03,320 --> 00:41:05,040
but he's great at making others suffer.

744
00:41:14,560 --> 00:41:15,520
Come on, Qiu.

745
00:41:15,520 --> 00:41:16,920
I asked you to light the stove,

746
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:18,080
not fire up a train engine.

747
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:18,920
This smoke...

748
00:41:19,400 --> 00:41:20,560
This coal only makes smoke.

749
00:41:20,560 --> 00:41:21,560
- What is this?
- No flame at all.

750
00:41:21,720 --> 00:41:22,840
What can I do about it?

751
00:41:22,840 --> 00:41:24,440
You keep pressing the coal, not the fire.

752
00:41:24,840 --> 00:41:26,160
How's it supposed to catch then?

753
00:41:26,160 --> 00:41:27,520
You need to poke it. See?

754
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:28,800
See? It's working now.

755
00:41:29,400 --> 00:41:31,560
I run the kitchen. I'm not the cook.

756
00:41:31,840 --> 00:41:33,200
Then get us a cook.

757
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:34,400
We're already short-handed.

758
00:41:34,400 --> 00:41:35,840
Now we've got thirty more mouths.

759
00:41:36,200 --> 00:41:37,440
How can we keep up with that?

760
00:41:37,440 --> 00:41:39,360
What makes you think I didn't ask?

761
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:40,360
So what did they say?

762
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:43,840
They told us to study Serve the People

763
00:41:44,280 --> 00:41:46,240
and learn from the model workers.

764
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,190
Master Song.

765
00:41:47,190 --> 00:41:48,080
Master Song!

766
00:41:48,080 --> 00:41:48,940
What?

767
00:41:48,940 --> 00:41:50,060
Oh my goodness.

768
00:41:50,200 --> 00:41:51,480
The oil's about to catch fire!

769
00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:52,520
I'm about to catch too. Here!

770
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:53,360
- Hurry, hurry.
- Qiu!

771
00:41:53,360 --> 00:41:55,000
Learn from the model workers now.

772
00:41:55,080 --> 00:41:57,040
♪They say♪

773
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:58,400
You're useless.

774
00:41:59,800 --> 00:42:03,840
♪We can get special treatment♪

775
00:42:04,520 --> 00:42:06,600
♪So then♪

776
00:42:06,600 --> 00:42:07,760
Just fetch water.

777
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:09,360
Stop singing!

778
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:12,520
You're just a cook now.

779
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:14,360
And you still talk all day long.

780
00:42:15,480 --> 00:42:17,480
All you do is sing, sing all day.

781
00:42:18,080 --> 00:42:19,000
You even put on makeup.

782
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:20,520
Trying to act, huh?

783
00:42:21,240 --> 00:42:22,320
Daydreaming again.

784
00:42:22,840 --> 00:42:24,280
What acting? I'm not acting.

785
00:42:25,080 --> 00:42:27,160
Sure, you're a mess already.

786
00:42:27,160 --> 00:42:29,560
I'm the fire-stoking girl now.

787
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:33,570
Yang Paifeng.

788
00:42:33,570 --> 00:42:34,440
Happy now?

789
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:36,080
Stop ruining Yang Paifeng for me.

790
00:42:36,080 --> 00:42:37,280
Cut that nonsense.

791
00:42:37,280 --> 00:42:39,120
You? Yang Paifeng? Seriously?

792
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:44,240
Yang Paifeng.

793
00:42:46,340 --> 00:42:47,200
Just look.

794
00:42:47,200 --> 00:42:50,520
Don't they look like a pack of monkeys?

795
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:53,720
Loose cannon teaching another amateur,

796
00:42:54,520 --> 00:42:56,440
and they still turn out half-baked.

797
00:43:05,020 --> 00:43:06,940
=The Lead=
(Preview)

798
00:43:09,210 --> 00:43:10,840
If you don't want to learn,
or endure this hardship,

799
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:11,870
speak up now.

800
00:43:12,120 --> 00:43:13,890
Countless people want to join our troupe.

801
00:43:14,460 --> 00:43:15,930
Are you bullying people or what?

802
00:43:15,930 --> 00:43:17,690
Why does my kid get two black buns,

803
00:43:18,030 --> 00:43:20,300
while the other kids each get
one black bun and one white bun?

804
00:43:20,770 --> 00:43:22,320
Aren't you rehearsing Hong Deng Ji?

805
00:43:22,510 --> 00:43:23,500
Hua Caixiang

806
00:43:23,500 --> 00:43:24,380
will play Li Tiemei.

807
00:43:24,380 --> 00:43:25,290
Mi Lan, Grandma Li.

808
00:43:26,570 --> 00:43:27,670
How do I look like Grandma Li?

809
00:43:27,930 --> 00:43:29,760
She's your granddaughter.

810
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:41,620
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

811
00:43:43,090 --> 00:43:47,930
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

812
00:43:49,370 --> 00:43:53,560
♪We met and brushed past♪

813
00:43:55,120 --> 00:44:02,420
♪Your shadow drifted out of sight♪

814
00:44:16,790 --> 00:44:20,540
♪The stove fire blazed in my dream♪

815
00:44:22,140 --> 00:44:27,710
♪Lit up the tracks of pearly tears♪

816
00:44:28,830 --> 00:44:32,890
♪In my dream, water sleeves flew♪

817
00:44:34,020 --> 00:44:39,610
♪Hiding a lifetime of love♪

818
00:44:40,770 --> 00:44:44,970
♪The Qinling Mountains
crossed the stage♪

819
00:44:46,010 --> 00:44:51,640
♪Spring water brewed strong wine♪

820
00:44:52,810 --> 00:44:57,500
♪Sheep moved through the valley♪

821
00:44:58,180 --> 00:45:03,350
♪It felt like a promise
from another life♪

822
00:45:04,020 --> 00:45:09,050
♪When I woke up and turned back♪

823
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:15,510
♪I wasn't sure where to go♪

824
00:45:15,890 --> 00:45:21,170
♪If I chose again, I'd still roam♪

825
00:45:22,120 --> 00:45:27,930
♪All over this sunlit plateau♪

826
00:45:27,930 --> 00:45:33,350
♪The dream ends; the curtain falls♪

827
00:45:33,900 --> 00:45:39,410
♪Moonlight washes off this stage makeup♪

828
00:45:39,960 --> 00:45:44,920
♪The one in the mirror wears gray hair♪

829
00:45:45,940 --> 00:45:51,220
♪Already sang all my joy and sorrow♪

830
00:45:52,020 --> 00:46:01,050
♪Already shouted across Qinchuan Plain♪
